From 0bbe998a5fd3b9244d3b28d61aca1ecd6b72b814 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marco Giunta <marco_giunta@outlook.it>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 11:39:58 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/7] ASoC: aw88399: extract shared device library

Extract the device-level functions from aw88399.c into a new shared
library module (aw88399-lib.c), following the pattern established by
CS35L41 (cs35l41-lib.c) for chips that need both ASoC and HDA drivers.

The library contains the chip initialization, firmware loading, playback
start/stop sequences, and all their internal dependencies (PLL checks,
DSP management, volume control, calibration, CRC verification, etc.).
The ASoC codec driver retains the ALSA controls, DAPM widgets, codec
probe/remove, calibration service, and I2C bus driver registration.

A new Kconfig symbol SND_SOC_AW88399_LIB is introduced. SND_SOC_AW88399
(the existing ASoC codec) selects it, ensuring no change for current
users. A forthcoming HDA side codec driver will also select the library
without pulling in the full ASoC codec module, avoiding a binding race
where the ASoC I2C driver could claim serial-multi-instantiate devices
before the HDA driver.

Functions that are called by both the library and the ASoC codec's
remaining code (DSP control, volume setting, calibration updates, mute,
and status helpers) are exported from the library.

This is a pure code movement with no functional changes. The moved
functions are identical to their originals in aw88399.c.

Signed-off-by: Marco Giunta <marco_giunta@outlook.it>
